<item>
            <title>[SPR-2510] form:errors tag doesn&apos;t render</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2510</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The ErrorsTag is not rendering despite there being errors present.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Have tracked this down to the following code in AbstractHtmlElementBodyTag.doEndTag():&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if (this.bodyContent != null) {&lt;br/&gt;
    renderFromBodyContent(this.bodyContent, this.tagWriter);&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
else {&lt;br/&gt;
    renderDefaultContent(this.tagWriter);&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The tag is written as &amp;lt;form:errors path=&quot;&lt;b&gt;&quot; /&amp;gt;, ie. without body content. this.bodyContent is *not&lt;/b&gt; null but instead this.bodyContent.getString() returns the empty string (at least in Weblogic 8.1). Thus the tag is never rendered.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The solution seems to be either to modify this check, or to implement ErrorsTag.renderFromBodyContent() to call renderDefaultContent().&lt;/p&gt;</description>
